{
  "doc_id": "prion_0697",
  "text": "We report a 25-year-old man with Creutzfeldt-Jakob disease (CJD) who had received dura mater embolization in the external carotid artery for a nasopharyngeal angiofibroma 90 months earlier.\nThe patient was heterozygotous (Met/Val) at codon 129.\nThis case suggests that dura mater embolization can be responsible for the CJD.",
